node.text:
My bucket list guide to Zakynthos, Greece is finally up on the blog! It has all my favorite photography spots, best things to do, and tons of yummy restaurants, and beautiful accommodations. I can honestly say it’s one of the more stunning places I’ve been, and I hope that if you ever have the chance to go this guide will help you plan the perfect trip. 🌞 💙 (save this post to keep it on your bucket list!) 

Also, thanks so much to everyone that sent me recommendations for places to stay and eat. I made sure to include the most popular ones in the post, since that’s not really my area of expertise. 🤓

Photos: @everchanginghorizon shot on Sony a7rIII #bealpha @sonyalpha

node.text:
I can’t remember the last time I did more than one or two nights in the backcountry. Can’t remember the last time my entire body ached. Or I didn’t impulsively reach for my phone at the slightest hint of boredom. That is, I couldn’t remember until this past week. And I have to say it felt good to be exhausted. To hurt. To lean into the boredom. To just be alive. In the moment. In nature.

Also… nothing has ever felt better than this water. Lol 💦

Also also… last slide is an unedited iPhone video. 😍

Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
When carousels first came out, I remember thinking that I’d never use the feature. Now I don’t know what I’d do without it… Turns out carousels are the perfect crutch for an indecisive person like myself. 😂 I couldn’t choose which photo I liked best (again), from this day out on the water in Greece. So I went with all three! Which one would you have picked?
-
Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
I think it's pretty safe to say that summer is officially here! And I don't know about you, but I can't think of a better place to escape the heat than up at an alpine lake. Last week it was way too hot in the van to sleep, so Quin and I got up at 3:30 am and decided it was as good a time as any to start hiking! Needless to say, it was the best decision we've made in a long time. 

Plus, it was the perfect opportunity to dust off some of my favorite outdoor gear! @Backcountry has some great 4th of July deals going on right now if you need anything for your summer adventures. Use JESS15 for 15% off your entire first order.(AD Some exclusions apply). #findyourbackcountry
-
Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
Last week after roasting in 100 degree temps down in the Sierras, I had to hop out of the van and fly home before @everchanginghorizon drove up to Lake Tahoe. Now I’m roasting at home in Seattle and would do pretty much anything to be out on this water. Apparently I have a real knack for jumping from one heat wave to another. 🤦🏻‍♀️🥵 Or maybe I’m just bringing the heat with me… 😉
-
Photos w/ @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
Last month when I did my outdoor gear Q&A it became clear that for a lot of people the price tag on outdoor gear feels prohibitive.(AD) So, I started looking for a partner that offers the same high-quality gear as specialty stores at more affordable prices. @Sierraofficial has top active and outdoor brands at 20-60% less than department and specialty store prices. When it comes to getting outside, it’s important to be safe, comfortable, and have fun! If you can achieve all that and epic savings, even better! @shopstylecollective
-
Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
Sometimes when I push myself way outside my comfort zone I have trouble remembering it afterward. I don’t know if it’s the spike of adrenaline or what. But whenever I see these photos, it’s sort of an out of body experience. Like watching a ghost of myself. It’s haunting. But I feel like it fits the vibe pretty well. 🧜‍♀️🎹
-
Photo: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
Every trip I’ve ever been on has shaped me in some way. But some destinations leave a bigger mark than others. And Kauai is definitely one of those special places! I’ll always remember standing on the Nā Pali Coast in the middle of the night, staring up into a sky so heavy with stars that I could almost feel their gravitational pull. Memories like that one always remind me of the transformative power of travel.

What trips have defined you? Share your #TravelMakesUs story by tagging @MarriottBonvoy and using the #TravelMakesUs hashtag. #ad

📍@SheratonKauaiCoconutBeach

node.text:
Travel has always played an important role in my life. But it wasn’t until last year when the world shut down that I really took the time to reflect on the transformative power of travel. I think in a lot of ways travel is the yin to our everyday yang. Without which it’s hard to appreciate what’s right in front of us. I’m grateful for every travel experience I’ve had because travel has broadened my worldview. But also because travel has taught me how to love the place I call home and the people who are waiting for me when I return.

What trips have defined you? Share your #TravelMakesUs story by tagging @MarriottBonvoy and using the #TravelMakesUs hashtag. #ad
